    "summary": "Janwillem Schrofer is an independent professional, who - through Valtana Consultancy - is active in the cultural sector, with a strong accent on artists and art organisations (residencies, museums,etc.) and educational institutes. He:\nCOACHES individual artists and other creative professionals on career choices and projects. COACHES art students through Workshops on 'Positioning'(Groningen, Enschede, Arnhem, Utrecht, Amsterdam, The Hague). \nCONNECTS creative professionals in all continents depending on the nature of their plans, using existing and new networks (CEAC, Europan, Prix de Rome, RA/RAIN, Res Artis) including his personal one built up over decades. \nCOUNSELS cultural organizations on strategy, cooperation, project development and selection through: Consultancy, working groups and through Executive Coaching (Designhuis Eindhoven, HKU Utrecht, Wander Den Haag, OCAT/Shenzhen, Geyonggi/Zuid-Korea, Tokyo Wonder Site, KAdE Amersfoort, VUmc Amsterdam, KABK Den Haag a.o.).\nCONTRIBUTES to cultural organizations and art projects through boardmembership of philanthropic and other foundations (Chinese European Art Center, Pauwhoffonds, Van Bijleveltstichting, Rijksakademie Artists' Endowment Fund, Gijselaar-Hintzenfonds, Steunfonds Haags Historisch Museum, Teor\u00eda y Pr\u00e1ctica de las Artes/Buenos Aires).\nAUTHOR of 'Plan and Play, Play and Plan: Defining Your Art Practice', Valiz Publishers, Amsterdam 2018. He is an Organizational Sociologist (Erasmus University Rotterdam, 1971)",
